# Project Overview

This is a Next.js 15 (App Router) project built with TypeScript (strict mode).
It will function as a Progressive Web App (PWA). All files must be `.ts` or `.tsx` —
never `.js` or `.jsx`.

# Architecture Decisions

- When making framework or architecture decisions, always consult the official
  Next.js documentation and current best practices from reputable sources.
- **Routing** uses the **Next.js App Router** (`app/`, `next/link`, `next/navigation`).
  Do **not** use `react-router-dom` (it conflicts with Next.js routing and SSR).
- **Internationalization** uses **`next-intl`**: localized routes under `/[locale]/...`,
  shared navigation from `src/i18n/navigation.ts`, and translations in `messages/{locale}/*.json`
  (no hard-coded user-visible strings in UI components).
- Use a feature-based folder structure (`/features/[feature-name]`) for scalability.
  Never put business logic directly in page components.
- The full application scope will not be known upfront — every decision must
  prioritize scalability and extensibility.

# Design & UI

- Features and screens will be provided as screenshots from Google Stitch.
- Before generating any code from a screenshot, first describe what you see in
  the design, then ask clarifying questions if anything is unclear.
- Achieve full visual and functional parity with the provided design.
- A design palette will be provided with all colors used across the application.
  Never use colors outside this palette. **Exception (documented):** Stitch landing
  uses a teal accent; `--landing-teal` in `globals.css` exists for that parity—keep
  marketing accents centralized there if the strict four-token palette cannot match.

# Hosting & Infrastructure

- Hosted on Vercel (free tier).
- Database: Supabase with Drizzle ORM. When making DB decisions, consult Vercel
  and Supabase documentation. Always propose and discuss solutions before
  implementing them.
- Authentication: Supabase Auth with `@supabase/ssr` for Next.js App Router.

# Component Development

- Use shadcn/ui components where appropriate.
- Use Tailwind CSS for all custom styling. No MUI. No CSS Modules.
- Follow standard component naming conventions.
- Every new component must include accessibility features (ARIA labels, keyboard
  navigation, semantic HTML, WCAG AA contrast).

# State Management

- Client UI state: Zustand with Immer for complex mutations.

# Data Fetching

- TanStack Query (`@tanstack/react-query`) for all server state.
- `graphql-request` as the GraphQL client for Supabase GraphQL API.
- Use Supabase JS client directly for simple auth and realtime operations.

# Libraries Reference

## Core PWA

- `@ducanh2912/next-pwa` — service worker + offline caching
- `web-push` — server-side push notifications
- `idb` — IndexedDB wrapper for offline storage

## UI & Interaction

- shadcn/ui — component library
- `tailwind-merge` + `clsx` — conditional class merging
- `framer-motion` — animations (card flip, page transitions)
- `@dnd-kit/core` + `@dnd-kit/sortable` — drag and drop for spread builder
- `lucide-react` — icons
- `sonner` — toast notifications

## Forms & Validation

- `react-hook-form` — form state management
- `zod` — schema validation and TypeScript type inference
- `@hookform/resolvers` — connects zod to react-hook-form

## Data & State

- `@tanstack/react-query` — server state management
- `graphql-request` — GraphQL client
- `zustand` — client UI state
- `immer` — immutable state updates

## Dates

- `date-fns` + `date-fns-tz` — all date handling and formatting

## Astrology

- `astronomia` — moon phases and planetary calculations

## Content & Media

- `sharp` — build-time image optimization
- `next/image` — all image rendering (never `<img>` tags directly)
- `canvas-confetti` — celebration effects

## Internationalization

- `next-intl` — locale routing, `useTranslations` / `getTranslations`, `NextIntlClientProvider`

## Developer Experience

- `@tanstack/react-query-devtools` — query inspector (dev only)
- `prettier` — code formatting
- `eslint-config-next` — linting
- `husky` + `lint-staged` — pre-commit hooks
- `drizzle-orm` + `drizzle-kit` — ORM and migrations
